20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Pav%20Stojkovic%2C%20former%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3Echief%20people%20officer%20of%20the%20sports%20publication%20The%20Athletic%2C%20the%20biotech%20startup%20Omeat%2C%20and%20other%20companies.%20He's%20now%20taking%20a%20career%20break%20to%20care%20for%20his%20newborn%20son.%20This%20story%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20worked%20as%20a%20chief%20people%20officer%20for%20over%20a%20decade%2C%20and%20I've%20had%20to%20lay%20off%20hundreds%20of%20people.%20I've%20seen%20layoffs%20go%20well%2C%20poorly%2C%20and%20everything%20in%20between.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20an%20emotional%20component%20that%20comes%20with%20getting%20let%20go.%20Even%20if%20the%20company%20offers%20generous%20severance%20or%20pays%20for%20COBRA%2C%20the%20initial%20reaction%20for%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20is%2C%20'I've%20put%20so%20much%20of%20myself%20into%20this%20job%2C%20and%20this%20is%20how%20they%20treat%20me%3F'%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20feeling%20is%20valid.%20But%20you%20can't%20let%20that%20emotion%20drive%20you%20to%20do%20something%20irrational.%20I've%20been%20yelled%20at%20point-blank%20to%20my%20face.%20Doing%20that%20just%20opens%20you%20up%20to%20all%20kinds%20of%20issues.%20In%20that%20moment%2C%20I'm%20less%20willing%20to%20be%20flexible%20and%20meet%20you%20where%20you%20are.%20My%20job%20is%20to%20get%20you%20to%20sign%20a%20piece%20of%20paper%20and%20get%20rid%20of%20you%20as%20fast%20as%20possible%20because%20you've%20gone%20from%20a%20good%20actor%20to%20a%20liability%20to%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dd010f6d-ca35-4512-8f9c-e58c8cfd7fcb%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDon't%20bash%20the%20company%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20example%20of%20an%20irrational%20move%20is%20publicly%20bashing%20the%20company.%20Your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-you-need-to-know-about-severance-agreements%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eseverance%20agreement%3C%2Fa%3E%20might%20have%20a%20non-disparagement%20clause%2C%20so%20if%20you%20speak%20negatively%20about%20the%20company%2C%20you%20could%20nullify%20your%20cash%20severance%2C%20an%20acceleration%20of%20your%20stock%20options%2C%20or%20your%20health%20insurance%20for%20you%20and%20your%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20or%20worse%20could%20happen%20if%20you%20take%20confidential%20information%20with%20you%2C%20such%20as%20by%20forwarding%20an%20email%20from%20your%20work%20account%20to%20your%20personal%20email%20on%20your%20last%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESay%20you%20post%20bad%20things%20about%20the%20company%20on%20your%20Facebook%20page.%20As%20a%20chief%20people%20officer%2C%20if%20I%20see%20it%2C%20I%20have%20an%20obligation%20to%20go%20to%20my%20CEO%20and%20say%2C%20'What's%20the%20actual%20risk%20to%20us%20here%3F'%20Most%20employers%20are%20smart%20enough%20to%20know%20when%20employees%20are%20just%20venting.%20But%20it's%20always%20on%20a%20case-by-case%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225cf425bf-4594-43a2-9790-0aa2f20e74a5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20can%20and%20should%20negotiate%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDon't%20sign%20anything%20immediately.%20I've%20seen%20former%20employees%20just%20sign%20whatever%20is%20given%20to%20them%20on%20the%20spot.%20Instead%2C%20say%20something%20like%2C%20'Thank%20you.%20I'm%20going%20to%20take%20these%20documents%2C%20review%20them%2C%20and%20get%20back%20to%20you.'%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20always%20have%20the%20ability%20to%20negotiate.%20As%20a%20chief%20people%20officer%2C%20I'm%20never%20going%20to%20say%2C%20'You%20know%20what%3F%20Because%20you're%20negotiating%2C%20now%20you%20get%20nothing.'%20That%20doesn't%20make%20sense%2C%20because%20I%20want%20you%20to%20sign%20that%20document.%20I%20want%20you%20to%20release%20the%20company%20from%20any%20potential%20risk%20and%20liability.%20So%20you%20have%20leverage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20asking%20for%20m